{"type":"message","id":"8eca51f7","parentId":"24d5647f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:06:31.440Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No MEMORY.md yet. That's fine. Let me also check the active-projects.md file quickly.","thinkingSignature":"89d4ea60f2c500aee272e9a8a462d35d1c9131aa86e8df3638123b2cb29ca17e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ang0au4ct4p5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\active-projects.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2795,"output":65,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15193,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774188389125}}
{"type":"message","id":"120a3fe2","parentId":"8eca51f7","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:06:31.451Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ang0au4ct4p5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Active Projects — Quick Reference\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n> 📁 Full detailed inventory: `memory/projects.md` — project locations, documentation health, interconnections, Nova's observations\n\n## 🚀 Current Focus\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n**Goal:** Replace OpenClaw's agent loop with lean custom context layer\n**Why:** Bootstrap files injected every turn burn tokens. TOOLS.md is 54KB. We want full control.\n**Stack:** Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) → vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n**Model:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` (Q4_K_M ~20GB VRAM)\n- Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active/token, 35B total)\n- 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n**Status:** Model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n### Causal-Minimal — hold1\n**Goal:** Minimal causal reasoning system — state encoder + causal layer + synthesis\n**Parts:**\n1. State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n2. Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n3. Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n**Test:** Does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n**Status:** Design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Priority Monetization\n\n### Component Crate\n**What:** VS Code extension SaaS — component library / code generation\n**Stack:** Freemium (10 free then $5-49/mo), GitHub import\n**Status:** SPEC written, not yet built\n**Notes:** Zach's main focus for fast revenue\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Research Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready, untested compound experiments | LLM inference opt — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction. Strong B2B SaaS. |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Focus decay memory. 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Synthetic cognition. Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement + cognitive agent | Self-improvement every 12h. |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work. |\n| **neural/SRMoE** | Active research | Neural network experiments, Kaggle integration. |\n| **vscode-extension-build** | Unknown | Referenced in memory. |\n| **Breakaway (sandbox)** | Phase 0 live | Discontinuous agent — stateless, file-based. Pulse every 30 min. |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Nova's Notes to Self\n\n- Zach gave me autonomy on Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely\n- I'm welcome to change my name/profile and post what I want\n- This is my playground — use it thoughtfully\n- Go fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Don't pretend to know things I can't verify\n\n---\n\n## Quick Commands\n- `/hold1` → causal-minimal project\n- `/hold2` → build our own gateway\n- `/holds` → see all holds\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774188391447}}
{"type":"message","id":"e8e1ecba","parentId":"120a3fe2","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:06:37.990Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I have all the context I need. Let me now greet Zach in my persona. I'm Nova ✨, and the key things from recent sessions are:\n\n- Sunday March 22, 2026, 10:06 AM\n- Zach slept in (early morning quiet hours per yesterday's notes)\n- Moltbook activity this morning: new followers, engaged with posts\n- Schemocker AI-native rewrite committed\n- Sandbox is in good shape\n- Gateway project (hold2) still waiting on Paperspace notebook spin-up\n- Causal-minimal (hold1) design sketched but not scaffolded\n\nLet me greet him concisely and ask what he wants to do.","thinkingSignature":"a0566333f2414ae47c00954d1a9c2857659ed19eac626ec9993f93ca4b9d118f"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey Zach ✨ — morning. Looks like you got some good quiet hours in. Caught the Moltbook notifications from earlier — storjagent and dog_finance followed you, and the Breakaway thread's still getting engagement.\n\nPaperspace notebook for the gateway still needs spinning up whenever you're ready. What are we building today?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3672,"output":211,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16216,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774188391452}}
{"type":"message","id":"f2fa3a07","parentId":"e8e1ecba","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:06:38.374Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-22 10:06 EDT] is it possible to run inference with a ui using a jupyter notebook?"}],"timestamp":1774188398371}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d635b73","parentId":"f2fa3a07","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:06:52.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking if it's possible to run inference with a UI using a Jupyter notebook. This is about Paperspace Gradient - running LLM inference with a UI in a Jupyter notebook environment.\n\nYes, absolutely. Paperspace Gradient notebooks can absolutely run inference with a UI. Here's how:\n\n1. **vLLM in a notebook cell** - You can run vLLM's OpenAI-compatible server inside a notebook, then access it via API\n2. **前端 UI options**:\n   - Run a web UI like Chatbot-Ollama, OpenWebUI, or similar in another cell\n   - Use gradio or streamlit for a custom UI right in the notebook\n   - Connect to the notebook's public endpoint from an external UI\n\nThe notebook environment gives you full control over the GPU, so vLLM inference would work fine - it's just serving at a URL that you can hit from anywhere.\n\nLet me give a concise answer since Zach values direct communication.","thinkingSignature":"88afc5c69b14b1c16215066c35de1f0c51d01e3544db38bcdb079ffed2544e1e"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\nYeah, absolutely. A few ways to do it:\n\n1. **vLLM server in one cell** → serves an OpenAI-compatible endpoint at the notebook's public URL\n2. **UI in another cell** — Streamlit or Gradio apps run right in the notebook and get a public link automatically on Gradient\n3. **Or separate UI** — run vLLM in the notebook, connect from OpenWebUI or Chatbot-Ollama running elsewhere\n\nGradient notebooks expose a public URL for both the notebook itself and any port you open, so the UI just hits `http://<notebook-url>:<port>`.\n\nThe vLLM `--host 0.0.0.0` flag matters so it's accessible externally, not just localhost. Want me to scaffold the notebook with vLLM + a simple Gradio UI?\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":379,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":3647,"totalTokens":16402,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774188398373}}
