{"type":"message","id":"cc56c224","parentId":"9666687b","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:46:44.194Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants a separate Paperspace instance, not using the same GPU machine. That makes sense - a lightweight CPU instance for the browser is cheaper and doesn't compete with the inference work.\n\nHe has Gradient notebooks, so he's familiar with the Paperspace ecosystem. He probably wants to use Paperspace Core (their cloud compute product) or just spin up a Linux VM through Gradient.\n\nI should ask:\n1. Does he want a Paperspace Core machine (separate from Gradient notebooks)?\n2. Or does he want me to set something up through the notebook interface?\n\nActually, Paperspace has:\n- **Gradient** - notebooks and deployments\n- **Core** - VMs and infrastructure\n\nFor a persistent browser with noVNC, we'd want a Core VM since it's a full Linux environment, not a notebook.\n\nLet me ask about the specific setup approach - does he want me to help set it up through the Paperspace console, or does he already have a Core machine he wants to use?\n\n\nHe probably just needs guidance on spinning up a Core VM and getting the necessary tools installed.","thinkingSignature":"5e8ff043490f88480bde96886baa22df3b774d3567be0f57f2d1b175aa5757c5"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\nSmart — keep the browser box separate so it doesn't compete with GPU resources.\n\nPaperspace Core is what you want (not Gradient). You can spin up an Ubuntu VM with like 4 vCPUs + 8GB RAM — cheap, around $10-15/mo.\n\n**Quick plan:**\n1. Create a Core machine (Ubuntu 22.04)\n2. I SSH in and install: `chrome`, `xvfb` (virtual display), `noVNC` (browser-accessible desktop)\n3. You get a URL — open it in Chrome, we both see the same browser\n4. I have full CDP control + can run terminal commands alongside it\n\n**To get started:**\n- Go to [console.paperspace.com](https://console.paperspace.com) → Core → Create Machine\n- Pick Ubuntu 22.04, 4 vCPU, 8GB RAM, assign a public IP\n- When it's up, give me the public IP + SSH key or password\n\nOnce I have credentials, I'll take it from there.\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":440,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":17345,"totalTokens":17828,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774190780271}}
