{"type":"message","id":"0aacffc8","parentId":"550edd70","timestamp":"2026-03-22T14:47:18.988Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to set up the Paperspace Core machine myself. He said \"you get to set it up yourself\" - so I need SSH access to his Paperspace Core account. Let me ask for credentials or an API key so I can provision the machine and access it.\n\nActually, let me think about this. Paperspace has an API. I could use the Paperspace API to:\n1. Create a Core machine\n2. Get the IP and access credentials\n\nBut I'd need API credentials for that. Let me ask Zach for his Paperspace API key or for access to provision the machine.\n\nOr maybe I should ask if he already has a Core machine running, or if he wants me to walk him through creating one first.\n\n\nI need to clarify what Zach means by \"launch the chrome dev server together\" - is he referring to the CDP server itself, or something else? And I should ask for his Paperspace credentials so I can actually provision and access the machine.","thinkingSignature":"ff03fbd04aeb946909dfde2d2f713d77fc340af941cd4affaa958f53da7b0aaa"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\nOn it. To provision and access the machine myself, I need:\n\n1. **Paperspace API key** — from [console.paperspace.com/settings](https://console.paperspace.com/settings) (API section)\n2. **Or** — if you've already got a Core machine spun up, just give me the public IP + SSH key\n\nOnce I have that, I'll:\n- Create the Ubuntu Core machine via the API\n- SSH in\n- Install Chrome + xvfb + noVNC\n- Start the CDP debug port\n- Give you a shareable URL\n\nWhat do you have ready?\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":332,"cacheRead":17484,"cacheWrite":166,"totalTokens":18025,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774190828367}}
