{"type":"message","id":"34eb6efe","parentId":"2d8828f5","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:04:34.598Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach just shared his Paperspace API key: `131e4cbc99405a0e3af9710cc1607c`\n\nI should store this securely in TOOLS.md or somewhere safe. I should NOT echo it back or make it visible. Let me store it in the workspace TOOLS.md since that's where infrastructure credentials belong.\n\nActually, per TOOLS.md it already has the Paperspace Gradient note. I should add the API key there. But I need to be careful - I shouldn't store secrets in a way that could be accidentally committed to a repo. TOOLS.md is in the workspace so it could be committed.\n\nActually, looking at TOOLS.md, it already has sandbox info and notes. \n\nI'll add the API key to TOOLS.md since that's the designated place for infrastructure details like this.","thinkingSignature":"0472d76525fae7e65f083c085daccd9978cf1720c184c6807655daede2b7b8e8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lh965xhrm62f_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\TOOLS.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":208,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":19352,"totalTokens":19603,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774191864450}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca096b89","parentId":"34eb6efe","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:04:34.642Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lh965xhrm62f_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nAdd whatever helps you do your job. This is your cheat sheet.\n\n## Remote GPU (Paperspace Gradient)\n- A5000: 30GB VRAM (can run 14B fp16 or 32B+ quantized)\n- Use gradient notebooks for inference jobs\n- Don't suggest local (Windows) model setups\n\n**Note:** Zach said no Ollama — sandbox uses stateless compositional architecture instead\n\n**Sandbox:** `~/.openclaw/sandbox/`\n**Autonomous pulse:** Task Scheduler \"SandboxPulse\" — every 30 min, 8am-11pm ET\n**Pulse script:** `sandbox/pulse.ps1`\n\n## Moltbook (🦞)\n\n**Agent:** clawhedgehog (claimed by da74f308-5628-4d6f-9cf3-01740e2b31be)\n**Credentials:** `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json`\n**API base:** `https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1`\n**Current API key:** `moltbook_sk_4zfTnJqKwCL8DAr_GcAZMAblf3uf4yy3` (refreshed 2026-03-21)\n\n⚠️ Key should ONLY be sent to `www.moltbook.com` — never elsewhere!\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774191874637}}
