{"type":"message","id":"07a3c0ab","parentId":"a6f23f11","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:09:11.202Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need a Gradient notebook spec file. Let me look at how Gradient notebooks work. The typical way to run a custom Docker container on Gradient is through a \"Docker runtime\" notebook. The user would:1. Create a new notebook\n2. Select \"Custom Docker\" as the runtime\n3. Point to a Dockerfile or image\n\nActually, Gradient has a feature where you can specify a Dockerfile in your notebook YAML. Let me create a proper Gradient notebook spec.\n\nFor Gradient, I should create a notebook file that Gradient can run. The format is typically YAML with a `docker` field pointing to a Dockerfile or a Docker image URL.\n\nLet me also think about whether we can just use the Gradient base notebook with a Dockerfile FROM gradient-base or if we need something else.\n\n\nI'm realizing the approach might be simpler—just give Zach a Dockerfile and notebook YAML that he can use to create a Gradient notebook with the Docker runtime, pointing to this workspace location where the Dockerfile lives. The user creates a notebook with Docker runtime and points to the Dockerfile in the workspace, which Gradient will build and run. Though I'm not entirely certain about the exact workflow without more details on their specific Gradient setup, so let me just provide the necessary files and clarify the next steps.","thinkingSignature":"6451cf28598efc379dad618ec93e231d56aa44f8cd78cb0049d4acb4a4f6512f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5rzyamhwjti2_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Gradient notebook spec for Nova Browser\n# Runtime: Docker\n# File: nova-browser.yaml\n\nname: nova-browser\ndocker:\n  image: nova-browser\n  build_context: ./nova-browser\n  dockerfile: Dockerfile\n  registry: \"\"  # Leave blank to build from local Dockerfile\n\nmachine_type: CPU-only\n\n# Ports to expose (Gradient will give you URLs)\nports:\n  - 8080  # noVNC web interface\n  - 9222  # Chrome DevTools\n\n# Startup will be handled by the Dockerfile CMD\n# The noVNC URL will be: https://<notebook-url>/vnc.html?autoconnect=1\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\nova-browser\\gradient-notebook.yaml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":15292,"output":447,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28072,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774192138712}}
