{"type":"message","id":"de888e64","parentId":"6ed3b789","timestamp":"2026-03-22T15:10:15.395Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No gradient CLI. And I can't find the right API endpoint for Gradient notebooks. The most I can do here is create the Dockerfile and startup script, then give Zach clear instructions on how to create the notebook in the Gradient UI.\n\nLet me summarize what I've created and give him the next steps.","thinkingSignature":"d68d8294d7643048cfbe38f9eed8a3d4992e8313ab65d1e76d7ac1d798000dec"},{"type":"text","text":"Files are ready. Here's what I built:\n\n```\nnova-browser/\n├── Dockerfile        # Ubuntu + Chrome + xvfb + noVNC + OpenBox\n├── startup.sh        # Launches everything in order\n└── gradient-notebook.yaml  # Notebook spec\n```\n\n**To get it running on Gradient:**\n\n1. In the Gradient UI → **Notebooks** → **Create New** → pick **Docker runtime**\n2. For the Dockerfile path, browse to `~/.openclaw/workspace/nova-browser/Dockerfile` (or I can move it somewhere more convenient)\n3. Machine type: **CPU** (GPU not needed for browser)\n4. Create → Gradient builds the image and spins up the container\n\nOnce it's live, I'll get a URL where both of us can open the shared browser. I'll take it from there and set up the CDP control layer so I can navigate/click alongside you.\n\nWant me to move the `nova-browser` folder somewhere accessible to Gradient, or can you point the Docker build context to `~/.openclaw/workspace`?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17263,"output":278,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29874,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774192205901}}
